{"CONTORT":[{"def":"To twist, or twist together; to turn awry; to bend; to distort; to wrest.","pos":""}],"CONTORTED":[{"def":"Twisted, or twisted together.","pos":""}],"CONTORTION":[{"def":"A twisting; a writhing; wry motion; a twist; as, the contortion of the muscles of the face.","pos":""}],"CONTORTIONIST":[{"def":"One who makes or practices contortions.","pos":""}],"CONTORTIVE":[{"def":"Expressing contortion.","pos":""}],"CONTORTUPLICATE":[{"def":"Plaited lengthwise and twisted in addition, as the bud of the morning-glory.","pos":""}],"CONTOUR":[{"def":"The outline of a horizontal section of the ground, or of works of fortification.","pos":""}],"CONTOURNE":[{"def":"Turned in a direction which is not the usual one; -- said of an animal turned to the sinister which is usually turned to the dexter, or the like.","pos":""}],"CONTOURNIATED":[{"def":"Having furrowed edges, as if turned in a lathe.","pos":""}]}